p:
Will passive immunization with plasma from convalescent patients be beneficial for treating COVID-19? Anti-S antibodies seem to protect against lethal CoV challenge and clear the virus in mice and ferrets (
 Du et al., 2008a; 
 Du et al., 2007; 
 Du et al., 2008b; 
 Fett et al., 2013). In a small experiment, SARS-CoV-2 infection reportedly protected against a second challenge of macaques, which was attributed to the development of protective antibodies (
 Bao et al., 2020). The outcome of human clinical trials will, of course, outweigh animal-model experiments.
